  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the process of securing admission at MICA, Ahmedabad?",
  "response": "Securing admission to MICA (Mudra Institute of Communications, Ahmedabad) involves several steps. The process can vary slightly from year to year, so it's important to check the latest information on the official MICA website or directly from the admission office. Generally, the admission process for the flagship Post Graduate Diploma in Management - Communications (PGDM-C) program involves the following steps:\n\n1. **Eligibility Criteria**: \n   - You should have a bachelor's degree (10+2+3 system) or equivalent qualification in any discipline from a recognized university.\n   - Students appearing for the final year of the degree examination can also apply, provided they complete their degree by a specified date.\n\n2. **Entrance Exams**:\n   - You must appear for at least one of the following national-level management entrance tests: CAT (Common Admission Test), XAT (Xavier Aptitude Test), GMAT (Graduate Management Admission Test).\n  \n3. **Application Form**:\n   - Fill out the application form for MICA, which is usually available online on the MICA website. Pay the application fee as specified.\n\n4. **MICAT (MICA Admission Test)**:\n   - After registering, candidates are required to take the MICAT. It is an entrance test conducted twice a year by MICA. MICAT comprises sections including psychometric test, descriptive test, and sections on Verbal ability, Quantitative ability, General awareness, and Divergent-Convergent Thinking.\n\n5. **Shortlisting**:\n   - Based on your performance in the entrance exams (CAT/XAT/GMAT) and MICAT, MICA will shortlist candidates for the next round.\n\n6. **Group Exercise (GE) and Personal Interview (PI)**:\n   - Shortlisted candidates are invited to participate in the Group Exercise and Personal Interview rounds. These rounds assess your communication skills, creativity, analytical thinking, and overall suitability for the program.\n\n7. **Final Selection**:\n   - The final selection is made based on a composite score, which includes the entrance exam scores, MICAT score, performance in Group Exercise and Personal Interview, and marks secured in the past academic records. The exact weightage given to each component may vary.\n\n8. **Offer Letter**:\n   - Successful candidates will receive an offer letter from MICA detailing the next steps, including fee payment deadlines and enrollment details.\n\nIt is crucial to stay updated with the specific deadlines and requirements for the year you plan to apply, as the admission process may undergo changes. Checking the MICA website frequently or contacting the admissions office for the most current information is recommended.",
